# Git Commit Attribution

All commits in this repository **must** be authored and committed as:

- **Name:** `Chris Pop`
- **Email:** `chrisalexanderpop@gmail.com`

## Required practice

When creating commits (including amend, cherry-pick, rebase, or rewrite), always set author and committer explicitly so Cursor’s default agent identity is never used:

```bash
GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="Chris Pop" \
GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="chrisalexanderpop@gmail.com" \
GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="Chris Pop" \
GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="chrisalexanderpop@gmail.com" \
git commit -m "..."
```

Equivalent one-shot form:

```bash
git -c user.name="Chris Pop" -c user.email="chrisalexanderpop@gmail.com" commit -m "..."
```

## Rules

- Do **not** create commits as `Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any other Cursor service identity.
- Applies to the parent cloud agent **and** every subagent.
- If rewriting history to fix attribution, rewrite author **and** committer, then force-push only when the user has asked for a rewrite.
- Prefer keeping this attribution even when spawning subagents that commit — pass the same author/committer env vars or `-c user.name` / `-c user.email` in their instructions.
